children.subject: Thanks for letting us know- we are working with the registrar's office to figure out what is going on here. Stay tuned.

I'm currently signed up on the waitlist for lecture but have not been able to sign up for or waitlist any discussion sections. Should I be worried? Is there anything I should do in response to these changes?
For your discussion it should say "enrolled" and not be clickable. Don't click any other option and click continue. That worked for me.

Is there any way I can just change my Lab but not my Discussion? I tried on telebears but it cancels the transaction if I try to change only the lab time and I don't want to lose my spot in discussion.

history.content:
Dear Students; 
 
The Academic Senate has just approved a second hour of discussion for EE 16A. At the request of the faculty, a second hour of discussion has been added on Telebears. The second hour is linked with the first hour, so students who have already registered will see that this new hour has been added to their schedule.  It is possible that your discussion may now conflict with another class. Please log in to Telebears and review your schedule. 
 
If you would like to switch secondary sections (whether you are enrolled or wait listed) please use TeleBears to do so but to make sure that you don't lose your current spot, please read the following closely.
 
Whether you are currently enrolled in the course or wait listed, DO NOT drop the class and re-enroll to change sections; you will lose your place.  You will only need to log into TeleBears and click on "Switch Secondary Sections" and choose the lab and discussion that would suit your schedule. 

To switch a lab or discussion section while remaining in the primary (lecture) section of the class: Tele-BEARS will display a table of your current class schedule on which you can select the class for which you want to switch the lab or discussion section. A table of available lab or discussions will be presented, from which you can select your new choice. You must confirm the transaction before the section(s) can be switched.

For more detailed information regarding and other questions about TeleBears, please see this link: http://registrar.berkeley.edu/Registrar/tutor_telebears.html
 
 
If any of this is confusing, please don't hesitate to contact Sara Nevius at saranevius@berkeley.edu or stop by 205 Cory during open office hours. 
 
Thanks,
Sarah
history.subject: Important Update about EE 16A discussion sections
